## CROSS-PLATFORM UI CONSIDERATIONS

When implementing UI components:

1. ACCOUNT for platform differences:
   - Touch interfaces vs mouse interfaces
   - Screen size variations
   - Performance differences
   - Input method variations

2. ADAPT UI for different platforms:
   - Use responsive layout techniques
   - Provide alternative interactions for touch vs mouse
   - Scale UI elements appropriately
   - Test on target platforms

3. HANDLE platform-specific limitations:
   - Mobile: Optimize for touch and smaller screens
   - Web: Consider browser compatibility
   - Desktop: Leverage additional screen space
   - VR/AR: Consider spatial UI needs

SEE MORE: /docs/cross_platform_ui.md

## RESPONSIVE DESIGN

Implement responsive UI components:

1. USE relative sizing instead of fixed pixel values
2. IMPLEMENT adaptive layouts that respond to available space
3. PRIORITIZE content and hide secondary UI when space is limited
4. MAINTAIN usability across device sizes
5. TEST on both small and large screens

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// Responsive layout pattern
fn show_responsive_panel(&mut self, ui: &mut egui::Ui) {
    // Get available width
    let available_width = ui.available_width();
    
    // Determine layout mode based on available space
    let layout_mode = if available_width < 600.0 {
        LayoutMode::Compact
    } else if available_width < 1200.0 {
        LayoutMode::Standard
    } else {
        LayoutMode::Expanded
    };
    
    match layout_mode {
        LayoutMode::Compact => {
            // Stacked vertical layout for small screens
            ui.vertical(|ui| {
                self.show_toolbar(ui);
                self.show_content(ui);
                
                // Hide secondary elements in compact mode
                if ui.button("Show More").clicked() {
                    self.show_secondary_panel = true;
                }
                
                if self.show_secondary_panel {
                    self.show_secondary_content(ui);
                }
            });
        },
        LayoutMode::Standard => {
            // Side-by-side layout for medium screens
            ui.horizontal(|ui| {
                ui.vertical(|ui| {
                    self.show_toolbar(ui);
                    self.show_content(ui);
                });
                
                ui.separator();
                self.show_secondary_content(ui);
            });
        },
        LayoutMode::Expanded => {
            // Full layout with all panels for large screens
            ui.horizontal(|ui| {
                ui.vertical(|ui| {
                    self.show_toolbar(ui);
                    self.show_content(ui);
                });
                
                ui.separator();
                ui.vertical(|ui| {
                    self.show_secondary_content(ui);
                    self.show_tertiary_content(ui);
                });
            });
        }
    }
}
```

