## THEMING AND STYLING

For consistent UI styling:

1. USE EGUI's built-in theming system
2. FOLLOW the established Brush visual style
3. MAINTAIN consistent spacing and alignment
4. IMPLEMENT dark and light mode support
5. USE the defined color palette

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// UI theming pattern
pub fn configure_theme(ctx: &egui::Context) {
    let mut style = (*ctx.style()).clone();
    
    // Set up color palette
    let accent_color = egui::Color32::from_rgb(0, 120, 215);
    let background_color = egui::Color32::from_rgb(240, 240, 240);
    let text_color = egui::Color32::from_rgb(20, 20, 20);
    
    // Apply colors to existing theme
    style.visuals.widgets.noninteractive.bg_fill = background_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.noninteractive.fg_stroke.color = text_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.inactive.bg_fill = background_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.inactive.fg_stroke.color = text_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.hovered.bg_fill = background_color.lighten(0.05);
    style.visuals.widgets.hovered.fg_stroke.color = text_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.active.bg_fill = accent_color;
    style.visuals.widgets.active.fg_stroke.color = egui::Color32::WHITE;
    
    // Set spacing
    style.spacing.item_spacing = egui::vec2(8.0, 8.0);
    style.spacing.window_margin = egui::style::Margin::same(12.0);
    style.spacing.button_padding = egui::vec2(8.0, 4.0);
    
    // Apply the modified style
    ctx.set_style(style);
}
```

